%N A015552 a(n) = 6*a(n-1) + 7*a(n-2), a(0) = 0, a(1) = 1.
%C A015552 Number of walks of length n between any two distinct nodes of the complete graph K_8. Example: a(2)=6 because the walks of length 2 between the nodes A and B of the complete graph ABCDEFGH are: ACB, ADB, AEB, AFB, AGB and AHB. - _Emeric Deutsch_, Apr 01 2004
%C A015552 General form: k=7^n-k. Also: A001045, A078008, A097073, A115341, A015518, A054878, A015521, A109499, A015531, A109500, A109501. - _Vladimir Joseph Stephan Orlovsky_, Dec 11 2008
%C A015552 The ratio a(n+1)/a(n) converges to 7 as n approaches infinity. - _Felix P. Muga II_, Mar 09 2014
